---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Helm & Kustomize" 
  description="Interactive visualization of Helm chart structure, Go template rendering, release management, rollback mechanics, and Kustomize overlays"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { label: "Home", href: "/" }, 
    { label: "Kubernetes", href: "/kubernetes/" },
    { label: "Helm & Kustomize", href: "/kubernetes/helm/" }
  ]}
>
  <div class="viz-container">
    <header class="viz-header">
      <h1>⎈ Helm & Kustomize</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Chart Structure, Go Template Rendering, Release Management, Rollback & Kustomize Overlays</p>
    </header>

    <section class="overview-section">
      <div class="overview-card">
        <p>
          Raw Kubernetes YAML doesn't scale. When you have dozens of microservices across dev, staging, and
          production, you need a way to <strong>template</strong>, <strong>package</strong>, and
          <strong>version</strong> your manifests. <strong>Helm</strong> is the package manager for Kubernetes —
          it uses Go templates to generate manifests from reusable <em>charts</em>, tracks
          <em>releases</em> as versioned snapshots, and supports atomic upgrades with rollback.
          <strong>Kustomize</strong> takes a different approach: no templates, just pure YAML with
          <em>overlays</em> that patch a base configuration. Both solve the same problem — managing
          configuration variance — but with fundamentally different philosophies.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Helm Chart Structure -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>📁 Helm Chart Structure</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Click each file/directory to understand its role in a Helm chart.</p>

      <div class="chart-anatomy">
        <div class="chart-tree">
          <div class="tree-item" data-item="chart-yaml">
            <span class="tree-icon">📄</span> Chart.yaml
          </div>
          <div class="tree-item" data-item="values-yaml">
            <span class="tree-icon">⚙️</span> values.yaml
          </div>
          <div class="tree-item" data-item="templates-dir">
            <span class="tree-icon">📂</span> templates/
          </div>
          <div class="tree-item indent" data-item="tpl-deploy">
            <span class="tree-icon">📄</span> deployment.yaml
          </div>
          <div class="tree-item indent" data-item="tpl-service">
            <span class="tree-icon">📄</span> service.yaml
          </div>
          <div class="tree-item indent" data-item="tpl-ingress">
            <span class="tree-icon">📄</span> ingress.yaml
          </div>
          <div class="tree-item indent" data-item="tpl-helpers">
            <span class="tree-icon">📄</span> _helpers.tpl
          </div>
          <div class="tree-item indent" data-item="tpl-notes">
            <span class="tree-icon">📄</span> NOTES.txt
          </div>
          <div class="tree-item indent" data-item="tpl-tests">
            <span class="tree-icon">📂</span> tests/
          </div>
          <div class="tree-item" data-item="charts-dir">
            <span class="tree-icon">📂</span> charts/
          </div>
          <div class="tree-item" data-item="crds-dir">
            <span class="tree-icon">📂</span> crds/
          </div>
          <div class="tree-item" data-item="chart-lock">
            <span class="tree-icon">🔒</span> Chart.lock
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chart-info" id="chartInfo">
          <div class="chart-info-title">Click a file</div>
          <div class="chart-info-desc">Click any file or directory in the chart tree to learn what it does.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Go Template Rendering -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>🔧 Go Template Rendering</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">See how Helm transforms templates + values into final Kubernetes manifests. Edit values and watch the output change.</p>

      <div class="template-viz">
        <div class="tpl-columns">
          <div class="tpl-col">
            <div class="tpl-col-header">values.yaml</div>
            <div class="tpl-editor" id="valuesEditor">
              <div class="tpl-line"><span class="tpl-key">replicaCount:</span> <span class="tpl-val editable" id="valReplicas" data-field="replicas">3</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line"><span class="tpl-key">image:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">repository:</span> <span class="tpl-val editable" id="valImage" data-field="image">nginx</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">tag:</span> <span class="tpl-val editable" id="valTag" data-field="tag">1.25.3</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line"><span class="tpl-key">service:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">type:</span> <span class="tpl-val editable" id="valSvcType" data-field="svcType">ClusterIP</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">port:</span> <span class="tpl-val editable" id="valPort" data-field="port">80</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line"><span class="tpl-key">resources:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">limits:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent2"><span class="tpl-key">cpu:</span> <span class="tpl-val">500m</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent2"><span class="tpl-key">memory:</span> <span class="tpl-val">128Mi</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tpl-col">
            <div class="tpl-col-header">template</div>
            <div class="tpl-editor">
              <div class="tpl-line"><span class="tpl-key">apiVersion:</span> apps/v1</div>
              <div class="tpl-line"><span class="tpl-key">kind:</span> Deployment</div>
              <div class="tpl-line"><span class="tpl-key">metadata:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">name:</span> <span class="tpl-tpl">{`{{ include "mychart.fullname" . }}`}</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line"><span class="tpl-key">spec:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">replicas:</span> <span class="tpl-tpl">{`{{ .Values.replicaCount }}`}</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">template:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent2"><span class="tpl-key">spec:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent3"><span class="tpl-key">containers:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent3">- <span class="tpl-key">image:</span> <span class="tpl-tpl">{`{{ .Values.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.image.tag }}`}</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent4"><span class="tpl-key">ports:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent4">- <span class="tpl-key">containerPort:</span> <span class="tpl-tpl">{`{{ .Values.service.port }}`}</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tpl-col">
            <div class="tpl-col-header">rendered output</div>
            <div class="tpl-editor output" id="renderedOutput">
              <div class="tpl-line"><span class="tpl-key">apiVersion:</span> apps/v1</div>
              <div class="tpl-line"><span class="tpl-key">kind:</span> Deployment</div>
              <div class="tpl-line"><span class="tpl-key">metadata:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">name:</span> <span class="tpl-rendered">my-release-mychart</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line"><span class="tpl-key">spec:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">replicas:</span> <span class="tpl-rendered" id="outReplicas">3</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">template:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent2"><span class="tpl-key">spec:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent3"><span class="tpl-key">containers:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent3">- <span class="tpl-key">image:</span> <span class="tpl-rendered" id="outImage">nginx:1.25.3</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent4"><span class="tpl-key">ports:</span></div>
              <div class="tpl-line indent4">- <span class="tpl-key">containerPort:</span> <span class="tpl-rendered" id="outPort">80</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="action-bar">
          <button class="action-btn primary-btn" id="renderBtn">🔧 helm template</button>
          <button class="action-btn election-btn" id="setOverrideBtn">--set image.tag=2.0.0</button>
          <button class="action-btn reset-btn" id="resetTemplateBtn">↺ Reset</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Common Go Template Patterns -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>📐 Go Template Patterns</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Click each pattern to see how it works and when to use it.</p>

      <div class="patterns-grid">
        <div class="pattern-card active" data-pattern="if">
          <div class="pattern-name">Conditionals</div>
          <div class="pattern-syntax">{`{{ if .Values.x }}`}</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern-card" data-pattern="range">
          <div class="pattern-name">Loops</div>
          <div class="pattern-syntax">{`{{ range .Values.list }}`}</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern-card" data-pattern="with">
          <div class="pattern-name">Scope</div>
          <div class="pattern-syntax">{`{{ with .Values.x }}`}</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern-card" data-pattern="include">
          <div class="pattern-name">Named Templates</div>
          <div class="pattern-syntax">{`{{ include "name" . }}`}</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern-card" data-pattern="toYaml">
          <div class="pattern-name">YAML Helpers</div>
          <div class="pattern-syntax">{`{{ toYaml .Values.x | nindent 4 }}`}</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern-card" data-pattern="default">
          <div class="pattern-name">Defaults</div>
          <div class="pattern-syntax">{`{{ default "val" .Values.x }}`}</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern-card" data-pattern="tpl">
          <div class="pattern-name">Dynamic Templates</div>
          <div class="pattern-syntax">{`{{ tpl .Values.x . }}`}</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern-card" data-pattern="lookup">
          <div class="pattern-name">Cluster Lookup</div>
          <div class="pattern-syntax">{`{{ lookup "v1" "Secret" "ns" "name" }}`}</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pattern-detail" id="patternDetail">
        <div class="pattern-detail-title">Conditionals</div>
        <div class="pattern-detail-code">{`{{ if .Values.ingress.enabled }}`}<br/>apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1<br/>kind: Ingress<br/>...<br/>{`{{ end }}`}</div>
        <div class="pattern-detail-desc">
          Conditionally include entire resources or blocks. Falsy values: false, 0, "", nil, empty collections.
          Use <code>{`{{ if and .Values.a .Values.b }}`}</code> for compound conditions.
          The <code>{`{{- if ... }}`}</code> syntax (note the dash) trims leading whitespace to keep YAML clean.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Release Management -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>🚀 Release Lifecycle Simulator</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Install, upgrade, and rollback a Helm release. Watch how revision history and release state change.</p>

      <div class="release-sim">
        <div class="release-controls">
          <h3>Release: my-app</h3>
          <div class="config-group">
            <label>Chart Version</label>
            <select id="chartVersion" class="config-select">
              <option value="1.0.0">mychart-1.0.0</option>
              <option value="1.1.0">mychart-1.1.0</option>
              <option value="2.0.0">mychart-2.0.0</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div class="config-group">
            <label>Replicas: <strong id="relReplicasLabel">2</strong></label>
            <input type="range" id="relReplicasSlider" min="1" max="10" value="2" step="1" class="slider">
          </div>
          <button class="action-btn primary-btn" id="helmInstallBtn">📥 helm install</button>
          <button class="action-btn election-btn" id="helmUpgradeBtn" style="margin-top: 8px" disabled>⬆️ helm upgrade</button>
          <button class="action-btn chaos-btn" id="helmRollbackBtn" style="margin-top: 8px" disabled>⏪ helm rollback</button>
          <button class="action-btn reset-btn" id="helmUninstallBtn" style="margin-top: 8px" disabled>🗑️ helm uninstall</button>
        </div>

        <div class="release-display">
          <div class="release-status-bar">
            <div class="rel-status" id="relStatus">Not installed</div>
            <div class="rel-revision">Revision: <strong id="relRevision">—</strong></div>
          </div>

          <div class="release-events" id="releaseEvents">
            <div class="event-header">Helm Events</div>
          </div>

          <div class="revision-history" id="revisionHistory">
            <div class="rev-header">Revision History</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Helm Hooks -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>🪝 Helm Hooks</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Hooks let you run Jobs at specific points in the release lifecycle. Click each hook to learn when it fires.</p>

      <div class="hooks-timeline">
        <div class="hook-item" data-hook="pre-install">
          <div class="hook-dot"></div>
          <div class="hook-label">pre-install</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hook-line"></div>
        <div class="hook-item" data-hook="post-install">
          <div class="hook-dot"></div>
          <div class="hook-label">post-install</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hook-line"></div>
        <div class="hook-item" data-hook="pre-upgrade">
          <div class="hook-dot"></div>
          <div class="hook-label">pre-upgrade</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hook-line"></div>
        <div class="hook-item" data-hook="post-upgrade">
          <div class="hook-dot"></div>
          <div class="hook-label">post-upgrade</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hook-line"></div>
        <div class="hook-item" data-hook="pre-rollback">
          <div class="hook-dot"></div>
          <div class="hook-label">pre-rollback</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hook-line"></div>
        <div class="hook-item" data-hook="pre-delete">
          <div class="hook-dot"></div>
          <div class="hook-label">pre-delete</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hook-line"></div>
        <div class="hook-item" data-hook="test">
          <div class="hook-dot"></div>
          <div class="hook-label">test</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hook-detail" id="hookDetail">
        <div class="hook-detail-title">Click a hook</div>
        <div class="hook-detail-desc">Click any hook in the timeline to learn when it runs and common use cases.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Kustomize vs Helm -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>⚖️ Kustomize vs Helm</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Two philosophies for the same problem. Click each approach to compare.</p>

      <div class="compare-viz">
        <div class="compare-cards">
          <div class="compare-card active" data-approach="helm">
            <div class="compare-icon">⎈</div>
            <h3>Helm</h3>
            <div class="compare-tagline">Template-based packaging</div>
          </div>
          <div class="compare-card" data-approach="kustomize">
            <div class="compare-icon">🔧</div>
            <h3>Kustomize</h3>
            <div class="compare-tagline">Template-free overlays</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-detail" id="compareDetail">
          <div class="compare-table">
            <div class="compare-row header">
              <div class="compare-cell">Aspect</div>
              <div class="compare-cell">Helm</div>
              <div class="compare-cell">Kustomize</div>
            </div>
            <div class="compare-row">
              <div class="compare-cell label">Philosophy</div>
              <div class="compare-cell highlight">Parameterize with templates</div>
              <div class="compare-cell">Patch plain YAML</div>
            </div>
            <div class="compare-row">
              <div class="compare-cell label">Learning curve</div>
              <div class="compare-cell highlight">Go templates + Helm concepts</div>
              <div class="compare-cell">Strategic merge patches</div>
            </div>
            <div class="compare-row">
              <div class="compare-cell label">Packaging</div>
              <div class="compare-cell highlight">Charts (tgz archives)</div>
              <div class="compare-cell">Directories with kustomization.yaml</div>
            </div>
            <div class="compare-row">
              <div class="compare-cell label">State tracking</div>
              <div class="compare-cell highlight">Release secrets in cluster</div>
              <div class="compare-cell">None (stateless)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="compare-row">
              <div class="compare-cell label">Rollback</div>
              <div class="compare-cell highlight">Built-in (helm rollback)</div>
              <div class="compare-cell">Git revert + kubectl apply</div>
            </div>
            <div class="compare-row">
              <div class="compare-cell label">Ecosystem</div>
              <div class="compare-cell highlight">Artifact Hub, chart repos</div>
              <div class="compare-cell">Built into kubectl</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Kustomize Overlays -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>📂 Kustomize Overlay System</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">See how Kustomize patches a base configuration for different environments.</p>

      <div class="kustomize-viz">
        <div class="kust-columns">
          <div class="kust-col">
            <div class="kust-col-header">base/</div>
            <div class="kust-editor">
              <div class="kust-line"><span class="tpl-key">apiVersion:</span> apps/v1</div>
              <div class="kust-line"><span class="tpl-key">kind:</span> Deployment</div>
              <div class="kust-line"><span class="tpl-key">metadata:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">name:</span> my-app</div>
              <div class="kust-line"><span class="tpl-key">spec:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">replicas:</span> <span id="kustBaseReplicas">1</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">template:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent2"><span class="tpl-key">spec:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent3"><span class="tpl-key">containers:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent3">- <span class="tpl-key">name:</span> app</div>
              <div class="kust-line indent4"><span class="tpl-key">image:</span> <span id="kustBaseImage">my-app:latest</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent4"><span class="tpl-key">resources:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent5"><span class="tpl-key">limits:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent6"><span class="tpl-key">memory:</span> <span id="kustBaseMem">128Mi</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="kust-col overlay-col">
            <div class="kust-col-header">
              <select id="kustEnv" class="config-select inline-select">
                <option value="dev">overlays/dev/</option>
                <option value="staging">overlays/staging/</option>
                <option value="prod">overlays/prod/</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="kust-editor" id="kustOverlay">
              <div class="kust-line"><span class="tpl-key">namePrefix:</span> <span class="kust-patch" id="kustPrefix">dev-</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line"><span class="tpl-key">replicas:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent">- <span class="tpl-key">name:</span> my-app</div>
              <div class="kust-line indent2"><span class="tpl-key">count:</span> <span class="kust-patch" id="kustOverlayReplicas">1</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line"><span class="tpl-key">images:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent">- <span class="tpl-key">name:</span> my-app</div>
              <div class="kust-line indent2"><span class="tpl-key">newTag:</span> <span class="kust-patch" id="kustOverlayTag">dev-abc123</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line"><span class="tpl-key">patches:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent"><span class="kust-patch" id="kustOverlayPatch">memory: 128Mi</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="kust-col">
            <div class="kust-col-header">kustomize build output</div>
            <div class="kust-editor output" id="kustOutput">
              <div class="kust-line"><span class="tpl-key">apiVersion:</span> apps/v1</div>
              <div class="kust-line"><span class="tpl-key">kind:</span> Deployment</div>
              <div class="kust-line"><span class="tpl-key">metadata:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">name:</span> <span class="tpl-rendered" id="kustOutName">dev-my-app</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line"><span class="tpl-key">spec:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">replicas:</span> <span class="tpl-rendered" id="kustOutReplicas">1</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent"><span class="tpl-key">template:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent2"><span class="tpl-key">spec:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent3"><span class="tpl-key">containers:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent3">- <span class="tpl-key">name:</span> app</div>
              <div class="kust-line indent4"><span class="tpl-key">image:</span> <span class="tpl-rendered" id="kustOutImage">my-app:dev-abc123</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent4"><span class="tpl-key">resources:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent5"><span class="tpl-key">limits:</span></div>
              <div class="kust-line indent6"><span class="tpl-key">memory:</span> <span class="tpl-rendered" id="kustOutMem">128Mi</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="action-bar">
          <button class="action-btn primary-btn" id="kustBuildBtn">🔧 kustomize build</button>
          <button class="action-btn reset-btn" id="kustResetBtn">↺ Reset</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Helm Release Storage -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>🗄️ How Helm Stores Releases</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Helm stores release history as Kubernetes Secrets (or ConfigMaps). Click to explore the internals.</p>

      <div class="storage-viz">
        <div class="storage-flow">
          <div class="stor-component">
            <div class="stor-icon">⎈</div>
            <div class="stor-name">helm upgrade</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stor-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="stor-component">
            <div class="stor-icon">📦</div>
            <div class="stor-name">Render templates</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stor-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="stor-component">
            <div class="stor-icon">🔐</div>
            <div class="stor-name">Create Secret</div>
            <div class="stor-detail">sh.helm.release.v1.my-app.v3</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stor-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="stor-component">
            <div class="stor-icon">📤</div>
            <div class="stor-name">kubectl apply</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="stor-secret-detail">
          <div class="stor-secret-header">Secret: sh.helm.release.v1.my-app.v3</div>
          <div class="stor-secret-body">
            <div class="stor-field"><span class="stor-key">type:</span> helm.sh/release.v1</div>
            <div class="stor-field"><span class="stor-key">data.release:</span> base64(gzip(json))</div>
            <div class="stor-field indent"><span class="stor-key">→ chart:</span> metadata + templates</div>
            <div class="stor-field indent"><span class="stor-key">→ config:</span> merged values</div>
            <div class="stor-field indent"><span class="stor-key">→ manifest:</span> rendered YAML</div>
            <div class="stor-field indent"><span class="stor-key">→ info.status:</span> deployed | superseded | failed</div>
            <div class="stor-field indent"><span class="stor-key">→ version:</span> revision number</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Best Practices -->
    <section class="sim-section">
      <h2>🏆 Best Practices</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Practical guidelines for production Helm and Kustomize usage.</p>

      <div class="operators-grid">
        <div class="operator-card">
          <div class="op-icon">🔒</div>
          <h3>Pin Chart Versions</h3>
          <p>Always specify exact chart versions in CI/CD. Use Chart.lock for dependency pinning. Floating versions cause irreproducible deploys and midnight surprises.</p>
          <div class="op-crd">helm install --version 1.2.3</div>
        </div>
        <div class="operator-card">
          <div class="op-icon">🧪</div>
          <h3>Template Testing</h3>
          <p>Use helm template to render locally, helm lint for validation, and helm test for post-deploy smoke tests. Add unit tests with helm-unittest plugin.</p>
          <div class="op-crd">helm template + helm lint + helm test</div>
        </div>
        <div class="operator-card">
          <div class="op-icon">📋</div>
          <h3>GitOps with Kustomize</h3>
          <p>Store base + overlays in Git. Use Argo CD or Flux to reconcile. Kustomize's stateless nature makes it a perfect fit for declarative GitOps workflows.</p>
          <div class="op-crd">kubectl apply -k overlays/prod/</div>
        </div>
        <div class="operator-card">
          <div class="op-icon">🔄</div>
          <h3>Helm + Kustomize Together</h3>
          <p>Use Helm to package vendor charts, then Kustomize to patch for your environment. Argo CD supports this natively with the "helm + kustomize" source type.</p>
          <div class="op-crd">helmCharts: + patches: in kustomization.yaml</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

